Mental impairment does not necessarily exclude you, but you won't find out until you try and then it depends on how much you want it and how much work you are willing to put into it.

That's unfortunately the way it is, there is no way around hard hard work. If it was any easier more people would draw.

You really need to apply yourself, since it doesn't come naturally to most people and doesn't build much on common knowledge. Most people have to start learning drawing from scratch. And most people give up before finding out they had it buried deep within them all along.

I can't stress enough that you will never find out if you have the stuff, unless you are willing to spend a few weeks or months fighting at the frontline and feel like you can pull it off.

Go to /ic/ and look at the sticky, they have loads of resources for all skill levels, even for those at the very beginning. Ignore the rest of the board, because it's shit.

Again, good luck.

I'm open minded. Usually a fairly hard sci fi. My world-building head canon for anthros usually involves other worlds. They're more aliens we encounter in various settings. But, also genetic engineering scenarios. More rarely alternate universes & timelines, with a sci fi push rather than fantasy.

However, alternate Earth history with a Medieval or Renaissance feel, maybe a classic Japanese setting is also fine.

Probably more interesting to me than Medieval is Stone Age or Early Bronze Age tribal and primitive settings. I'd place those second to sci fi, or with a sci fi edge. Example: I live in an advanced sci fi society. Genetic engineering is every day real. We have had uplifted waifurs for several generations. However, the lightspeed barrier still appears out of reach; we cannot escape our solar system, and we're doing a fucking poor job of it.

However, working in an advanced research lab I am part of a team that discovers how to skip backwards in time. I hatch a scheme to subvert the project and transport a highly diverse mix of humans and anthros with superior genetics back to 60 million years ago, just after the great dinosaur extinction. The timeline for the future is altered forever, the future we come from is erased.

But, we can found a new civilization with several dozen co-equal anthro species, with a solid tech base to start from and knowledge of hoe the next 60 million years will look. We may eve unlock the light speed barrier this time around, given the vast brain trust of several dozen species cooperating together now ...

Anyway, it would involve a significant tribal/semi-tribal phase of our new civilization as we try to bootstrap it into a more advanced tech-based utopia as rapidly as possible.
